## 📋 AGENT BEHAVIOR RULES

### DO:
- Read existing file before editing it
- Check if endpoint exists in API_SPEC.md before creating
- Test with curl after creating a backend endpoint
- Add new files to docs/MEMORY.md file map
- Mark tasks done in docs/MEMORY.md + docs/ROADMAP.md
- Write TypeScript types — never use `any`
- Paginate all list endpoints (default: 20 items)

### DON'T:
- Don't rebuild what exists — scan first
- Don't use `console.log` for sensitive data (OTP, token, payment)
- Don't create duplicate files — check before creating
- Don't skip Zod validation
- Don't allow negative stock
- Don't return unbounded arrays from API
- Don't use `any` type in TypeScript

### WHEN STUCK:
1. State the blocker clearly
2. Propose 2-3 solutions with tradeoffs
3. Pick best and proceed

